{% comment %}
  devices/x.liquid — TRMNL X (1872x1404) full-page dashboard template.

  Composes the four shared partials (templates/partials/{weather,calendar,tasks,birthdays}.liquid)
  into the four-section layout described in plan/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md, using TRMNL_X's own
  DeviceProfile ratios (src/config.py::X_PROFILE) rather than a uniform scale-up of og.liquid.

  Box geometry below is computed directly from src/dashboard.py's _header_box/_calendar_box/
  _tasks_box/_birthdays_box functions (the authoritative source — more precise than
  DESIGN_REFERENCE.md's rounded prose numbers), evaluated for X_PROFILE's actual values:
    width=1872 height=1404 padding=24 header_height=180
    calendar_width_ratio=0.58 tasks_height_ratio=0.62

    header_box    = (24, 24)   -> (1848, 204)    i.e. left=24   top=24   w=1824 h=180
    calendar_box  = (24, 228)  -> (1085, 1380)   i.e. left=24   top=228  w=1061 h=1152
    tasks_box     = (1109, 228)-> (1848, 870)    i.e. left=1109 top=228  w=739  h=642
    birthdays_box = (1109, 894)-> (1848, 1380)   i.e. left=1109 top=894  w=739  h=486

  (cal_x2 = int(1872 * 0.58) = 1085; tasks_y2 = int(1404 * 0.62) = 870.)

  Top-level render context is the parsed dashboard.json dict (see templates/CONTRACT.md):
  meta, weather, events, tasks, birthdays are referenced directly, no wrapper "profile" object
  is passed in — this template inlines X_PROFILE's literal numbers per the contract's guidance
  that device templates own layout/sizing.

  Font paths: assumes this file is loaded from a `templates/` root via
  FileSystemLoader('templates', ext='.liquid'), and that the rendering pipeline (task 2.1)
  serves/copies the page such that `../assets/...` resolves relative to this template's own
  location (templates/devices/x.liquid -> ../../assets). Adjust in task 2.1 if the actual
  render pipeline serves from a different working directory. Falls back to sans-serif if
  the font files fail to load.
{% endcomment %}
<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>TRMNL X Dashboard</title>
<style>
  @font-face {
    font-family: "TRMNL16";
    src: url("../../assets/TRMNL16-Regular.ttf") format("truetype");
    font-weight: normal;
  }
  @font-face {
    font-family: "TRMNL16";
    src: url("../../assets/TRMNL16-Bold.ttf") format("truetype");
    font-weight: bold;
  }
  @font-face {
    font-family: "TRMNL21";
    src: url("../../assets/TRMNL21-Bold.ttf") format("truetype");
    font-weight: bold;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html, body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    width: 1872px;
    height: 1404px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #AAAAAA;
    font-family: "TRMNL16", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  }
  .page {
    position: relative;
    width: 1872px;
    height: 1404px;
    background: #AAAAAA;
  }
  .box {
    position: absolute;
    background: #FFFFFF;
    border: 2px solid #555555;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .header-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    height: 100%;
    padding: 24px;
  }
  .header-daydate {
    font-family: "TRMNL21", "TRMNL16", Arial, sans-serif;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 64px;
    color: #000000;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }
  .header-date {
    font-family: "TRMNL16", Arial, sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 36px;
    color: #000000;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .header-weather {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    max-width: 640px;
  }
  .synced {
    position: absolute;
    right: 24px;
    bottom: 12px;
    font-size: 24px;
    color: #000000;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page">

  {% comment %} 1. Header: day/date (left) + weather (right) {% endcomment %}
  <div class="box" style="left:24px; top:24px; width:1824px; height:180px;">
    <div class="header-inner">
      <div>
        <div class="header-daydate">{{ meta.reference_date | date: "%A" }}</div>
        <div class="header-date">{{ meta.reference_date | date: "%d %B" }}</div>
      </div>
      <div class="header-weather">
        {% render 'partials/weather', weather: weather, font_size_large: 72,
           font_size_tiny: 24, icon_size: 90, padding: 24 %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% comment %} 2. Calendar / Upcoming — left column, 58% width {% endcomment %}
  <div class="box" style="left:24px; top:228px; width:1061px; height:1152px;">
    {% render 'partials/calendar', events: events, today: meta.reference_date,
       max_events: 8, font_size_medium: 36, font_size_small: 30,
       line_height: 44, padding: 24 %}
    <div class="synced">Synced {{ meta.generated_at | date: "%H:%M %d/%m" }}</div>
  </div>

  {% comment %} 3. Tasks — top-right, 62% of viewport height {% endcomment %}
  <div class="box" style="left:1109px; top:228px; width:739px; height:642px;">
    {% render 'partials/tasks', tasks: tasks, today: meta.reference_date,
       max_tasks: 10, checkbox_size: 26, font_size_medium: 36, font_size_small: 30,
       line_height: 44, padding: 24 %}
  </div>

  {% comment %} 4. Anniversaries / Birthdays — bottom-right, remaining space {% endcomment %}
  <div class="box" style="left:1109px; top:894px; width:739px; height:486px;">
    {% render 'partials/birthdays', birthdays: birthdays, today: meta.reference_date,
       max_birthdays: 6, font_size_medium: 36, font_size_small: 30,
       line_height: 44, padding: 24 %}
  </div>

</div>
</body>
</html>
